<br>
I think each player has their own hate list. Now taunt may be able to match our hate list +1 with someone elses. But I still dont know about that. On an average raid you have at least 2 rogues. Ive messed around with rogues a bit, and they can gain nasty aggro even from a missed backstab. You dont even have to hit the mob and he can turn and start hitting you. <br>
<br>
There are some times when a player generates so much aggro that you just cant taunt the mob off them as well. If taunt were to add +1 to your list, wouldnt that pull the mob off? What about low HPs aggro? How many times have you been able to save a chanter on the verge of death by simply taunting? If they are across that frenzy line, you cant save em unless a cleric gets a heal off fast enough.<br>
<br>
Again..i think the only people who really know how hate, aggro, and taunt works are the folks at Verant. And they will probably never tell us. Maybe someone could ask at FanFaire in Vegas. Never know...get one of the devs all drunk and drill him with questions about it. heh heh <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/zummy2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=graalthedorf>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/03 12:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The taunt button, an anecdotal view.</span><hr size=1> If you really want to test the taunt skill, you have to do so with mobs that speak. Otherwise your results are conjecture. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
