<br>
I mean things like, does it work differently after a paladin's chain stunned a mob for a while to get huge hate, does it work differently with multiple melees engaged, or when the person who has aggro does/does not have enough hate to move the mob, or when they're not on top of the hate list?<br>
<br>
For your particular issue Britty, it should be easy to test: Just get a low level cleric to chain stun a mob a little, then taunt it off them and see how long it takes them to get aggro back by hitting it.  If taunt gives max hate + 1 the cleric should get aggro back in one swing, if not, I'd expect it would take them a long time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tarskxev>TarskXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/03 6:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The taunt button, an anecdotal view.</span><hr size=1> I've always been half of the opinion that the hate+1 theory is correct. I know mashing it all the way through the fight doesn't help any.<br>
<br>
As for 'catching up' hate, well I generally think that the probability of taunt being successful depends on:<br>
<br>
1) how far down from the top of the list you already are<br>
2) level difference between you and the mob<br>
3) Your taunt skill<br>
<br>
Which would explain why (on average) you can't taunt a mob that you're coming to fresh, when someone else has a ton of aggro, but that sometimes, very occasionally, the dice roll right, you get that 1000 out of 1000 and flick the mob onto you from the shaman.<br>
<br>
As for the required conditions to get a mob off you being your hate + a number, I do rather like that theory. it would explain the lack of tanking pingpong directly after a successful taunt.<br>
<br>
But really, it's all theories and we're just grasping at strawns <p>--<br>
