What if taunt gives you first place+20 instead of 1 ?<br>
Anyway, what i wanted to point here is:<br>
When you attack a speaking mob ( for examples, legionnaires in sanctus seru speaks when a successful taunt if on) and you're ALONE!!! (wich of course means you're already on top of hate list ) when i hit my taunt button, 2 only things can occur: <br>
1) i fail and dont get any message, but the mob is still beating on me ( normal, i'm the only one attacking him ).<br>
2) i have a successful taunt and i get something like: i'll teach you to mess with me, Kenn.<br>
<br>
Now what can we say? the mob only speaks when someone comes to the top of the hatelist? then why does it speak when you are already at the top?<br>
<br>
Second thing:<br>
<br>
I imagine the hate list being implemented like that:<br>
<br>
nameofplayer+hatenumber.<br>
<br>
Imagine player hits for 120, he would be put in the hatelist with a hatenumber of 120*aggromodifier (spells, position of the player compared to the mob, etc). Each swing, he gets his hatenumber being raised, and the mobs do sorting of his hatelist every round to see who he's supposed to beat on.<br>
If you taunt, you are put in position one, with your hatenumber being increased to be a little above the precedent number one.<br>
Now a list like that can explain why some people are able to lower their position in the hatelist. for example, a jolt casted by the ranger would have the effect of putting him 500points lower, without ever removing him from the hatelist.<br>
Add to this some sort of event triggered when someone in the aggro range of the mob has his life being too low. Some sort of shout saying:&quot; i'm nearly dead, come and send me to my bind point, plz&quot;.<br>
<br>
As a developper, i can imagine this as a very easy way to implement it, and would fit in the EQ reality.<br>
<br>
Now when i said that the mob was sorting his aggrolist every  round, i'm only giving an example, but i think the exact time can be found quite easely. For example, you take a slowed mob, get aggro of him (with a taunt), than everyone stops hitting at all.<br>
You ask your enchanter to tash it, and see. If the mobs turns immediately on enchanter, then the number is pretty low. if it doesnt, then it's based on the mob's attack round; wich is supposed to be very long due to the fact he's slowed.<br>
<br>
just my 2cp. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=357628&quot;">Kenn's profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.colinspornoextravaganza.com/tests/ke.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tassthegreat>tass the great</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/03 9:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I may have an answer....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's not very often at ALL that one single press of the taunt key is going to get agro back to you if they manage to gain huge amounts of agro before the tank has even started.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
i play a rogue, but perhaps i can offer some insight. developers working on the same project tend to think alike due to having to read each others code and concepts.  this leads me to believe that just maybe taunt has some parallels to evade.<br>
<br>
on a successful evade, we are lowered on the hate list by 500 points or directly to second place, whichever is larger.  this means that on each successful evade we are lowered by at least 500 points.  a cap if you will.<br>
<br>
now, perhaps taunt has somewhat of the same form of cap?  perpendicular of course, but a cap nonetheless.  consider this:<br>
<br>
on a successful taunt, the warrior is given 500 hate or thrown to the top, whichever is lesser.  this means that you cannot gain more then 500 hate with one successful taunt.  this would explain why you cant gain aggro from a sham that lands a slow on an incoming mob, or otherwise take aggro with one taunt when you are far behind.<br>
<br>
this still doesnt explain the meat of this discussion, but it could shed some light on a few points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brutultarewmarr>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 1095<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/03 9:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I may have an answer....</span><hr size=1> They never said that it just put you 1 hate point above the highest person on the list.  What they said was it puts you on the top of the hate list by &quot;a small amount&quot;.  It certainly makes sense that this &quot;small amount&quot; would increase as your skill goes up.  I wouldn't be suprised if it was taunt skill/4 or something like that (watch somebody quote this as fact 2 weeks from now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
An  EFP Fire beetle has about 15 hps...it wouldn't take much of a hate buffer to keep a 15 hp mob on you for it's entire life while some noob hits it a few times for 3 dmg with &quot;a club&quot; and misses it about 10 times.  <br>
<br>
Another common mistake people make is assuming that 1 dmg = 1 point of hate.  If a 750 damage nuke = 750 points of hate wizards would never be able to nuke.  You have to do considerably more than 1 dmg to get 1 point of hate or us warriors wouldn't ever be able to hold aggro from damage dealers. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325267">Brutul Vilesilencer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
