<br>
Beastlord<br>
Warrior<br>
Shaman<br>
Rogue<br>
Druid<br>
Cleric<br>
Necromancer<br>
Enchanter<br>
<br>
The fights i will talk about are all EXP related, no big names, just typical EXP mobs and the random named/quest mob.<br>
<br>
Typically the Shaman or BL will pull.  The warrior assists and hits with arrows on pull typically.  As the mob gets to melee range the warrior takes over with melee/taunt.  Now the warrior is well geared and has 11/17(Shadowheart) main and Frostbringer offhand.  Being that the warrior is my GF and is sitting right next to me we can chat easily, or I am boxing her.<br>
<br>
There are times that the warrior could stop attacking and hold agro for entire fight(we have dont this), and there are the times that no matter how much ya mash that taunt key and how much the FB proc, the mob will not turn away from the shaman/beastlord.<br>
<br>
We have found a few things that seem consistent, some if not all are pretty logical/simple.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Taunt doesnt seem to get you to top-hatelist  1, it seems variable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Mob level seems inportant.  For the simple reason that the higher the mob the better AC/HP/skills it has, I assume.  The warrior can tank dark blue and lower and even some whites with Windblade.  But get a yellow/red (non 60 mob) and she needs to use 1handers   taunt.  Assuming less hits with 2hander = less melee agro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Every proc/spell and even the taunt skill seems to have a hidden agro #, but its not a set #, its random (ie Slow might have 10-500 range).  Reason I say this, I have watched the warrior proc FB 5  times(FB being a good agro weapon according to many, the msg board included) on 1 mob, mash the taunt key the instant its available....yet the mob refuses to turn from a single slow.  And the next mob, 1 taunt or proc and the mobs is glued to the warrior.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>4)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  On the non warrior side (ie no Taunt skill), I use Scorpion Venom(1100 DOT) and Incapacitate (stat debuffer) to agro if I am the current tank.  The chanter in my crew is a RL friend and has the PoI chanter dagger that lowers agro from Tash.  But at times, when she uses tash I cannot for the life of me gain agro from her.  I have to chain cast Incapacitate or if all else fails, another DoT or two (high mana drain).  So this again leads me to think on the random hate #'s.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>5)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  On the rogue side of things, our rogue rarely gains agro unless he has to of tank /shudder.  So Evade seems to be working very well.  I can think of only 1 or 2 times that the rogue has had to turn attack off and let the warrior gain agro back.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>6)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Healing rarely seems to get agro for our crew.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>7)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Necro can FD if his DoTs get outta hand.  Seems to work well enough.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Snare has never been an agro problem for us, unless cast immediately.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Not that any of this helps, but it is a lot of fun to think about and stew over.  I also at one time though that mob lvl was more concrete than it truely is.  But our warrior has successfully &quot;taunted&quot; lvl 60  mobs.  According to info, non 60 warriors cannot taunt 60  mobs, I dont disagree with this info, but I do know that she can hold agro on 60  mobs with a proc or just by DPS.<br>
<br>
I have to lean towards the +random hate # theory with my typical findings.  Of course other set-ups and gear will have different results, but I spend hours with this crew and its like this all the time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
