<br>
realistically the entire game is based on a huge database.....<br>
each zone is a different process.....trust me it is......<br>
<br>
zone into somewhere.....grab all player information and add to the zone.<br>
<br>
zone has a table of mobs.<br>
<br>
mob table has a hate table......it is a lit of mobs PCs/mobs that interact with it..<br>
<br>
mob is actually where the HATE TABLE EXISTS.....<br>
<br>
agro is determined linearly but accumulates on the MOB.....it does not decay it is ALWAYS there unless you zone out or are FD for more than 10 minutes i beleive....(1018 timeout rules apply somehow i beleive)<br>
<br>
<br>
now think about the mob movents and work on the basis that anyone entering the hate table enters with a token amount....i think this would be the average hate of the top 6 list<br>
<br>
this is why if you slow without tashing with a chanter the shammy is normally in trouble...<br>
<br>
taunt will put you at the top of a list with a token amount....<br>
<br>
this amount is dependant on your taunt skill....<br>
<br>
<br>
now mobs will only run to a player outside of melee range if A none is inside melee range with a hate amount with a said amount...<br>
<br>
inside melee range the number is actually smaller which is why rangers get jolt...<br>
<br>
the fact jolt exists means that the hate table does exist <br>
<br>
the linear application of jolt would be a negative hate number...<br>
<br>
memblur also proves hate tables exist....they are server side tho so we cant cut it apart and predict...<br>
<br>
melee damage adds agro  we know that missing doesnt...<br>
<br>
the fact higher levels taunt better is because we dont lose our lead on the hate table so badly as our hit rates go up and we also hit ALOT more than a pally/SK because of dual weild.....<br>
<br>
some 2hs are now overpowering our hit ratio advantages...(windblade)<br>
<br>
taunt does take you to the top of the list plus a token number but i find it also does fail....<br>
<br>
as a 63 warrior i can actuall take agro off any melee class with one taunt if i outdamage them regardless of what they do...(pally stun doesnt count as hate isnt addded when a mob is stunned i dont beleive)<br>
<br>
id say that all the examples given are actually completely right...<br>
<br>
a lvl 10 character will probably not generate enough taunt. generate 200 hate doing sub 20 damage on a mob that has 250 hps ( orc04 at orc1 in EC )<br>
<br>
a lvl 10 character prolly will never be able to use taunt to gain agro for any extensive ammount of time because there melee damage and taunt skill would not put them any where near far enough to contend with chain casting in an xp group...this is why at low levels MOST warriors get PING PONG in groups with a tasher slower and snarer....by the time they get to land a taunt without a spell landing just after it the mobs half dead from other melee and you hacking into it while its running about  ( think back to your days in DL and remember how you mezzed every add or rooted it because you couldnt stop it from killing the cleric with taunts...<br>
<br>
all the rules seem to work if you substitute some values into the process BUT no static values seem to work for all....<br>
<br>
i would expect its a reasonably simple trigger to move mobs from hitting one person to another<br>
<br>
<br>
ie<br>
o<br>
on hate = &gt; 200 on melee range = swap agro onto and hunt it down<br>
on have = &gt; 400 on Not melee range = swap and hunt him Down<br>
<br>
note NON-MELEE damage is not worked out the same way atm whic is actually specifically being targeted for nerf...apparently the test server has a version running but its apparently the same as melee piercing atm so they have alot of small tuning on 2H piercing damage on test server to create a new damage type...<br>
<br>
now if you add a few level variable into the formulaes you actually get a much truer scale....<br>
<br>
ie a 55 cleric will get more heal agro than a 60 cleric......i think that the anomolous errors in all our theories that pop up is because hate is using a level variable in the systems as well as skill and mob variables...<br>
<br>
basically what i do in xp groups seems to work very very well<br>
<br>
hit the mob  run bac to cam hit the mob for 3 seconds wait for whatever spells to land in the first wave....normally tash and slow....and sometimes a enthusiatic ranger ( i dont like early snaring it screws as they chain cast it if resists and generally get people killed)  <br>
<br>
once the mob has RUN to someone i hit taunt 1 time get agro because i am generating nice hate with 17&amp; 18 delay weapons at lvl 63..<br>
<br>
from here i light a cigarette and what the red bars....if someone does some special and gets agro i hit taunt again and mob turns back......only 1 time in 4 days have i had to taunt more than 3 times on any normal encounter....most only 2.  in duos i only hit taunt once after slow but thats expected i guess...<br>
<br>
the only time i think this doesnt really work is when the casters dont stop casting or sit/low health agro.... <br>
<br>
....something i have a little bit of a query on tho that you may want to help me with...<br>
<br>
what exactly is a TICK?  its used as the timing system for spells and i assume its also used in some way for the application of hate to the table....i justify this answer because i never get agro on a taunt if there are spells landing one after another..  it wont pingpong normally but it hits the same person and ignores the taunt...<br>
<br>
thus i get the slower to cast at same time as slower as tash lands faster and slow hits  then i see...  a mobbie YAWNS   then i hit taunt and all is well<br>
<br>
anything landing after yawns within say 2-3 seconds seems to stop the mob from turning....this may be a animation lag etc but it seems to hit the person in this time so i beleive that spells to some extent overwrite taunt ....this could be part of the equation for hate <br>
<br>
ie ...hate = &gt; that 200 to next person for last 2 ticks = mob turns and hits...<br>
<br>
now obviously it has to be applied in a loop basis there is no doubting that...the loop process may be triggered on a hit etc but with raids etc i wouldnt expect that to be very efficeient so taking a segment of time as the applying time would be....<br>
<br>
if atick is 1 second then maybe its applied ever half a tick....?<br>
<br>
it explains why health changes in chunks.....<br>
