umber to your own hate list. When someone attacks, nukes, slows, there is a chance they will be raised on hate list, similar to a resist roll. <br>
<br>
It is why sometimes a person can hit taunt once and get aggro or sometimes it takes 4 times. Its why when I nuke even though the warrior has only taunted I may or may not get aggro, same for when I slow. It is why no matter how many tests you work with they will all show different results because there isn't a set amount, its random. And because depending on the person taunting and where they are on the hate list, sometimes they get aggro back immediately and other times it takes longer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chrometalon>ChromeTalon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/03 4:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3015.topic&index=21>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:Comment</span><hr size=1> A bit from the Ranger perspective.<br>
<br>
To me it looks like the whole bloody mess is linear.  <br>
<br>
Flame Lick, Ensnare, and Taunt are always are close reach.  And I do add in Tangling Weeds when I'm the one tanking.  <br>
<br>
The DoT component of Flame lick does a great job generating agro, even when compared to high damage DoTs.  This makes me think that the DoT component is highly based on the actual &quot;Hit&quot; a mob takes every tick, not only the damage caused.<br>
<br>
If the Taunt button moves you up in a non-linear fashion then the effect of Tangling Weeds would not be able to keep agro on me after two successful taunts.  It does.  In fact, if I land Weeds and Ensnare a few times along with Flame Lick it's unlikely that a pure taunt will pull the mob off thru the rest of the fight.  According to the Top +1 theory a warrior should be able to catch up within a few taunts.  Not without Jolt they won't.<br>
<br>
Simply put, I can generate so much agro in the first 20 seconds that no matter what you do it will not come off me (unless I want it to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  I used to use a friend Rogue as a dot in this fashion while I just ran around shooting the mob full of arrows. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The whole agro thing is actually really hard to put into words.  It's just one of those things us Rangers have to learn to survive.<br>
<br>
